						               													<description> The Chang Er system lies at an important jump nexus and must be secured. The populace is not affiliated with the Synod of Worlds and presents us with an opportunity to win over some allies in this long war. The xeno-liguistics and xeno-sociology advisors to the fleet have entered into a limited dialogue with the leaders of the Chang. The Chang are a martial meritocracy and value strength and power while abhoring weakness. The Chang are also an honor bound society so an overt demostration of power like an orbital strike would be seen not only as a threat but as a cowardly act.&amp;#10;The Chang have agreed to send observers to the fleet in order to get a first hand look at our war with the Synod. Thses observers would like to watch our conduct and report back to the Chang Overlord as to our honor and trustworthiness. They have suggested the Synod held Zakar system as a site suitable for this demostration.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Lynchpin is the 3rd in a series of campaigns to liberate the Hevan Sector from the oppressive and genocidal rule of the Synod of Worlds. &amp;#10;It provides 4 scenarios detailing the Raid on the research facility located on the planet Anhur in the Zakar system. &amp;#10;It is compatible with Gruntz 15mm.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
